                <h1 class="section-title">The beginning</h1>
                <p>As we commemorate the centenary of the departure of the Peredvizhniki movement, and society once again calls for increased artistic attention to the ever-diminishing realities, we strive to revive the contemporary spirit of the Peredvizhniki movement – realism in service to the ordinary. Through the love of art and the digital form of touring exhibitions, we aim to break the boundaries of space and time, entering the lives of people.</p>
                <p>At this critical moment when there is an urgent need for the resurgence of the Peredvizhniki spirit, we anticipate rekindling the art ideals that departed from us a century ago. Through the “touring” exhibition format, we seek to evoke the artistic philosophy of a bygone era, reshaping humanism, and reviving its modern artistic embodiment – an emphasis on art that also cares about real-life issues. Thus, we will organize a touring art exhibition in Moscow, showcasing the beauty and reality of our human existence.</p>
                <p>The exhibition will gather works from artists of different countries for display in the designated exhibition area in Moscow. The primary format of the exhibition is the “City Mobile Exhibition,” to be held both online and offline simultaneously.</p>
            </section>
            
