                <p>Artworks should capture themes such as humanity, humanism, family, empathy, and the theme of “loving others.” These interdisciplinary artistic themes possess the unique ability to represent and reconnect with a non-hostile facet of “human life.”</p>
                <p>We invite a variety of artistic forms, including music, painting, dance, and photography, pushing beyond conventional boundaries. However, the dissemination of works will take place through appropriate reproduction formats such as images, videos, or audio.</p>
